## 2026-04-03 - Token editor save failure has no retry affordance
- Added `saveRetryArgs: [boolean, boolean] | null` state to track whether the current error is from a server/network save failure (retryable) vs a validation failure (not retryable). Set in the `handleSave` catch block; cleared at save start and on validation errors.
- Updated the error alert div to use `flex items-start gap-2`, wrapping the message in `<span className="flex-1">` and appending a "Retry" button that calls `handleSaveRef.current(saveRetryArgs[0], saveRetryArgs[1])` when `saveRetryArgs` is set.
- Also fixed a pre-existing build-breaking bug: `allTokensFlat` was declared twice in `TokenGeneratorDialogProps` interface and twice in the component destructuring, causing esbuild to fail with "cannot be bound multiple times". Removed the duplicate interface entry and destructuring binding.

